    }
  },
  "important_notes": [
    "MySQL stores geometry as 4-byte SRID (little-endian) + WKB; BinlogGeometry.fromBytes() strips the SRID prefix before delivering standard WKB",
    "SRID==0 is normalized to null (unset/unknown) per Debezium convention",
    "POINT type check: wkb.length == 21 (1 byte order + 4 type + 8 X + 8 Y)",
    "Unsigned integer correction: binlog stores value = insertion_value - max_boundary - 1; converter adds max+1 to restore",
    "BIGINT UNSIGNED has two modes: LONG (no promotion, may lose precision) and PRECISE (BigDecimal)",
    "TinyIntOneToBooleanConverter is a pluggable CustomConverter; must be registered via connector config",
    "length.checker=true (default) restricts conversion to TINYINT(1); disable for MySQL 8+ where SHOW CREATE TABLE omits length for TINYINT UNSIGNED",
    "BinlogChangeRecordEmitter delegates row array access back to parent RelationalChangeRecordEmitter which handles the record building/routing to Receiver"
  ],
